{
  "texts": [
    "The think-aloud protocols have been a brilliant method in cognitive and psychology studies and usability Data-Driven Hypothesis Generation in Clinical Research testing ever since they were introduced by Ericson and Simon 55.",
    "Although we recognize that this is the best strategy, we could use to capture the hypothesis generation process, the approach is not perfect, and there are limitations.",
    "The think-aloud protocol can only capture conscious processes articulated by participants.",
    "Therefore, we could say that our study revealed part of the process, not yet the whole cognitive process.",
    "It is potentially impossible to reveal the complete cognitive process of scientific hypothesis generation with our available technologies and approaches, a challenge beyond our current capacity."
  ]
}